abstract: United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit rules 2013 Wisconsin abortion law requiring physicians to have admitting privileges at nearby hospitals unconstitutional.
lead_paragraph: A 2013 state law that requires abortion providers to get admitting privileges at nearby hospitals is unconstitutional, a federal appeals court panel ruled Monday.

headline.main: Wisconsin: Appeals Court Blocks Abortion Law
